<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="349" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/109: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica (<persName type="from">Eberhardt</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-15T14:00:00-06:00">November
                                    15, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 4:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>70. Minister <persName corresp="#p_PL1">Pacheco</persName> called to
                            inform me confidentially that principally to further his own prestige in
                            Central America he is endeavoring to secure permission from President
                                <persName corresp="#p_JOR1">Jiménez</persName> to proceed to
                            Guatemala to confer with President <persName corresp="#p_UGJ1">Ubico</persName> for the purpose of calling a conference of
                            emissaries from the co-signers of the 1923 Treaty of Peace and Amity
                            with a view to forthwith denouncing the treaty and recognizing the
                                <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Martínez</persName> régime.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>